Hi,

Please see on huge picture (confluence-errormessage-plugin.repository.png). This is current error message in Repository plugin.

I mean use HTML strip function on each alert message. Alert can not display tags, only <br /> you can transform to \n (new line character). See on strip-errormessage.png, I hope more usable message for users.

You can use this function for example:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
function userAlertGlobalError( responseText )
{
	var error = responseText;

	//show only stack
	var search = "<b>Cause:</b>";
	error = error.substring( error.indexOf( search ) + search.length, error.length );
	error = error.replace(/(<([^>]+)>)/ig,""); //strip <tag>
	error = error.substring( 0, Math.min( error.length, 700 ) ); //remove duplicate new lines

	alert( "System error .... "
		+ "Reason:" + error + " ..." );
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

By the way, error stack on huge picture you can reproduce, If upgrade "Blogging RPC Plugin" in after install vanilla Confluence 2.3.3.

Thanks for implement.

Cheers,
Libor

